"{\"uid\": \"foxnews.com-live-news-olympics-2024-paris-august-4-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"This material may not be published, broadcast, rewritten, or redistributed.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 75, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a92026 FOX News Network, LLC.\", \"from\": 76, \"to\": 104, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 82, \"end\": 98, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FOX News Network\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 105, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Quotes displayed in real-time or delayed by at least 15 minutes.\", \"from\": 126, \"to\": 190, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Market data provided byFactset.\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Powered and implemented byFactSet Digital Solutions.Legal Statement.\", \"from\": 223, \"to\": 291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mutual Fund and ETF data provided byRefinitiv Lipper.\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 308, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6972073956654685e-27, \"text\": \"ETF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Exchange-traded_fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More medals will be handed out at the Summer Games on Sunday, August 4, as track and field athletes enter the field of play and swimmers head to pool.\", \"from\": 347, \"to\": 497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Suni Lee also returns to action on the uneven bars.\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 549, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 498, \"end\": 506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Suni Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sunisa_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Covered by:Ryan GaydosandRyan Morik  Coverage for this event has ended.\", \"from\": 551, \"to\": 622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 562, \"end\": 566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.6928061232806053, \"rank\": 0.443403828643388, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A United States Olympic shooter is reflecting on the future of the sport following her second consecutive run at the\\u00a0Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 624, \"to\": 755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mary Tucker, a\\u00a0Florida native\\u00a0currently residing in the Czech Republic, qualified to represent Team USA in the Women's Air and Smallbore Rifle competition at the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 757, \"to\": 949, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 757, \"end\": 768, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Tucker_(sports_shooter)\", \"score\": 0.8973980030468558, \"rank\": 0.11428571428571174, \"text\": \"Mary Tucker\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Tucker_(sports_shooter)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Tucker_(sports_shooter)\"}, {\"begin\": 819, \"end\": 827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9479947075273777, \"rank\": 0.054822019089376006, \"text\": \"Republic\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 852, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9991219372502151, \"rank\": 0.0007696141567084099, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 943, \"end\": 948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999455477969682, \"rank\": 5.445516820700463e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's nice to come from a country that takes so much pride in sports,\\\" Tucker told Fox News Digital.\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 1051, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1022, \"end\": 1028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trip_Tucker\", \"score\": 0.9998841280669325, \"rank\": 0.00011587773050679892, \"text\": \"Tucker\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trip_Tucker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trip_Tucker\"}, {\"begin\": 1034, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"score\": 0.999810089904525, \"rank\": 0.00018232192078726956, \"text\": \"Fox News\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fox_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I always say that I like representing the U.S.A. because it's one of those powerhouse countries in sports, in most things, but in sports especially.\\\"\", \"from\": 1052, \"to\": 1202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tucker, who won a silver medal at the Tokyo Games in 2021, soared over shooting's viewership at the 2024 Games, though she is concerned about the future of the Olympic sport.\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1378, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1204, \"end\": 1210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trip_Tucker\", \"score\": 0.9460256455696624, \"rank\": 0.057053770810840614, \"text\": \"Tucker\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trip_Tucker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trip_Tucker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is always talk of whether [shooting] is going to be taken out of the Games,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1473, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's kind of something that always looms.\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I think it's important for people to realize, and especially people who are fans of sports, that sport shooting and other\\u00a0types of shooting\\u00a0are fairly different.\\\"\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1681, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tucker said \\\"it's a very safe sport\\\" despite similarities to the basic principles.\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1683, \"end\": 1689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trip_Tucker\", \"score\": 0.9460256455696624, \"rank\": 0.057053770810840614, \"text\": \"Tucker\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trip_Tucker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Trip_Tucker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is an excerpt from a report by Gabriele Regalbuto.\", \"from\": 1767, \"to\": 1822, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1812, \"end\": 1821, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regalbuto\", \"score\": 0.9999999145779875, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Regalbuto\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regalbuto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Regalbuto\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The\\u00a0opening ceremony of the Olympics\\u00a0was immediately under criticism, and it \\\"saddened\\\" Pope Francis.\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1912, \"end\": 1924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Pope Francis\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19546\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pope_Francis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A statement released\\u00a0by the Vatican\\u00a0Saturday evening said there should be \\\"no allusions ridiculing the religious convictions of many people.\\\"\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 2068, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Holy See was saddened by certain scenes during the opening ceremony of the Paris Olympic Games and can only join the voices that have been raised in recent days to deplore the offence caused to many Christians and believers of other religions,\\\" the statement said.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2274, \"end\": 2284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9447702231601416, \"rank\": 0.04721784460344773, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"At a prestigious event where the whole world comes together to share common values, there should be no allusions ridiculing the religious convictions of many people.\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The freedom of expression, which is clearly not called into question here, is limited by respect for others.\\\"\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony turned heads when it included a headless\\u00a0Marie Antoinette\\u00a0early on, then a m\\u00e9nage \\u00e0 trois.\", \"from\": 2619, \"to\": 2722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2673, \"end\": 2689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5182076870013777e-18, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, what made critics most angry was when the ceremony appeared to depict a mock Last Supper with people dressed in drag.\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is an excerpt from a report by Ryan Morik.\", \"from\": 2852, \"to\": 2899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2888, \"end\": 2892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.9966921750037161, \"rank\": 0.00299757957354029, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles\\u00a0is just trying to soak in the moment.\", \"from\": 2901, \"to\": 2951, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles has further cemented her legacy as one of the greatest gymnasts of all time after she took home the gold medal in the women's vault final on Saturday, marking her third gold medal of the\\u00a02024 Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 2953, \"to\": 3166, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles will be 31 by the time the Los Angeles games come around, and while she's shown no signs of slowing down in Paris, that's certainly considered \\\"elderly\\\" in gymnastics.\", \"from\": 3168, \"to\": 3341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3201, \"end\": 3212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999697703651863, \"rank\": 2.865468205415143e-05, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 3282, \"end\": 3287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999281973516353, \"rank\": 7.180780419018409e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But again, Biles is still rewriting the history books, and just wants to enjoy it.\", \"from\": 3343, \"to\": 3425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, she took a subtle shot at, perhaps, the media and just about everyone else who asks a specific question.\", \"from\": 3426, \"to\": 3534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"you guys really gotta stop asking athletes what's next after they win a medal at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3536, \"to\": 3631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"let us soak up the moment we have worked our whole lives for,\\\" the now seven-time Olympic gold medalist\\u00a0posted on X Sunday.\", \"from\": 3632, \"to\": 3755, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It sure remains to be seen what Biles' future holds, and it is intriguing to wonder what is next, considering her continued dominance.\", \"from\": 3757, \"to\": 3891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But one can not blame her for wanting to take it all in.\", \"from\": 3893, \"to\": 3949, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was an excerpt from a report by Ryan Morik.\", \"from\": 3951, \"to\": 3999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3988, \"end\": 3992, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.9999770726336613, \"rank\": 2.2845618965726356e-05, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Scottie Scheffler\\u00a0shot a bogey-free course record 62 at Le Golf National on Sunday for a come-from-behind gold medal victory.\", \"from\": 4001, \"to\": 4126, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4001, \"end\": 4018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Scottie Scheffler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\"}, {\"begin\": 4057, \"end\": 4073, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Golf_National\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Golf National\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Golf_National\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Golf_National\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sure, the impact of the victory will have on his all-time legacy may not be up there with his\\u00a0two green jackets\\u00a0or even his two Ryder Cup victories.\", \"from\": 4128, \"to\": 4276, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it's no secret that this was his most emotional reaction to a victory.\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4351, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While standing on the podium for the medal ceremony, Scheffler burst into happy tears during the playing of the national anthem.\", \"from\": 4353, \"to\": 4481, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4406, \"end\": 4415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"score\": 0.9999999999998863, \"rank\": 1.2469524800660027e-13, \"text\": \"Scheffler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I get emotional in general.\", \"from\": 4483, \"to\": 4511, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Usually, I have a bit more time after a tournament to kind of reflect and compose myself, but with this one, you kind of go from one thing to the next,\\\" Scheffler told NBC shortly after the win.\", \"from\": 4512, \"to\": 4706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4665, \"end\": 4674, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"score\": 0.9999999999998863, \"rank\": 1.2469524800660027e-13, \"text\": \"Scheffler\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottie_Scheffler\"}, {\"begin\": 4680, \"end\": 4683, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"score\": 0.6205847965283888, \"rank\": 0.2698007307993835, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBC\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"You do not really reflect until you are standing up there on the podium.\", \"from\": 4707, \"to\": 4780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u2026\\\"  \\\"That was a pretty special moment I will remember for a long time: Standing up there on the podium with the gold medal around my neck,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 4781, \"to\": 4929, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The 27-year-old entered the clubhouse with a share of the lead at -19, but Tommy Fleetwood bogeyed 17 to drop a shot and could not chip in to force a gold-medal playoff.\", \"from\": 4931, \"to\": 5100, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5006, \"end\": 5021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tommy Fleetwood\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Fleetwood\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jon Rahm, who owned a share of the 54-hole lead, double-bogeyed late to all but put himself out of contention.\", \"from\": 5101, \"to\": 5211, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5101, \"end\": 5109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Rahm\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jon Rahm\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13156709\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Rahm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jon_Rahm\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taiwanese boxer Lin Yu-Ting, who previously failed a gender test, was guaranteed an Olympic medal from the\\u00a0Paris Games\\u00a0after the fighter defeated Bulgaria's Svetlana Kamenova Staneva via unanimous decision in the quarterfinals.\", \"from\": 5213, \"to\": 5440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5213, \"end\": 5222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\", \"score\": 0.9999999649578519, \"rank\": 3.3335873899796586e-08, \"text\": \"Taiwanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei\"}, {\"begin\": 5229, \"end\": 5240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-Ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 5359, \"end\": 5367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\", \"score\": 0.999994547273987, \"rank\": 5.45238731682484e-06, \"text\": \"Bulgaria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lin and Algerian boxer\\u00a0Imane Khelif\\u00a0have as faced scrutiny over a disqualification from the 2023 International Boxing Association (IBA) Women's World Championship.\", \"from\": 5442, \"to\": 5605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5450, \"end\": 5458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.966971466799806, \"rank\": 0.0338650591864536, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 5465, \"end\": 5477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421623295, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 5573, \"end\": 5576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 0.8289080598549244, \"rank\": 0.18903414432523905, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Both will now be at least bronze medal winners as there is no other match for losing semifinalists.\", \"from\": 5606, \"to\": 5705, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Lin was knocked to the canvas twice during the bout while Staneva took several punches to the face.\", \"from\": 5707, \"to\": 5806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Staneva faced boos during the bout and Lin was cheered following the announcement of the result, according to\\u00a0The Sun.\", \"from\": 5807, \"to\": 5925, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"International Olympic Committee president Thomas Bach defended having Lin and Khelif fight in the women's division on Saturday.\", \"from\": 5927, \"to\": 6054, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5927, \"end\": 5958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 5969, \"end\": 5980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Thomas Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What is going on in this context in the social media with all this hate speech, with this aggression and abuse, and fueled by this agenda, is totally unacceptable,\\\" Bach said.\", \"from\": 6056, \"to\": 6232, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6222, \"end\": 6226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"score\": 0.9996101238707316, \"rank\": 0.0003900281912794179, \"text\": \"Bach\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Johann_Sebastian_Bach\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amid the controversy, Lin\\u00a0received support\\u00a0from former Taiwanese President Tsai Ing-wen on social media Friday.\", \"from\": 6234, \"to\": 6345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6289, \"end\": 6308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_Republic_of_China\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Taiwanese President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_Republic_of_China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_Republic_of_China\"}, {\"begin\": 6309, \"end\": 6321, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsai_Ing-wen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tsai Ing-wen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsai_Ing-wen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tsai_Ing-wen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lin defeated Uzbekistan's Sitora Turdibekova via unanimous decision.\", \"from\": 6346, \"to\": 6414, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6359, \"end\": 6369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan\", \"score\": 0.9999996774233134, \"rank\": 1.4691979556001201e-07, \"text\": \"Uzbekistan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is an excerpt from a report by Ryan Gaydos.\", \"from\": 6416, \"to\": 6464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6452, \"end\": 6456, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.5625735825400193, \"rank\": 0.7774554124417481, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Olympic Committee (IOC) slammed the gender tests at the center of a controversy with two boxers fighting in the women's division - Imane Khelif and\\u00a0Lin Yu-ting.\", \"from\": 6466, \"to\": 6644, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6470, \"end\": 6507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6470, \"end\": 6507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6615, \"end\": 6627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421623295, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 6632, \"end\": 6643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The International Boxing Association (IBA) said in 2023 that Khelif and Lin were disqualified from the tournament for testing positive for \\\"XY chromosomes\\\" and have maintained that both fighters have an unfair advantage in the women's division.\", \"from\": 6646, \"to\": 6890, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6650, \"end\": 6682, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2449314785900427e-17, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 6684, \"end\": 6687, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.9877939164002353, \"rank\": 0.009552629893735816, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But IOC spokesman Mark Adams said Khelif and Lin were \\\"carted off and tested\\\" during the 2023 boxing world championships because \\\"there were suspicions against them.\\\"\", \"from\": 6892, \"to\": 7058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6896, \"end\": 6899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999999655529, \"rank\": 3.277250306271516e-11, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 6910, \"end\": 6920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"score\": 0.5137413298826524, \"rank\": 0.45833333333331644, \"text\": \"Mark Adams\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Adams_(basketball,_born_May_1956)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is a whole range of reasons why we will not deal with this,\\\" Adams said.\", \"from\": 7060, \"to\": 7139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Partly confidentiality.\", \"from\": 7140, \"to\": 7164, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Partly medical issues.\", \"from\": 7165, \"to\": 7187, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Partly that there was no basis for the test in the first place.\", \"from\": 7188, \"to\": 7251, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And partly data sharing of this is also highly against the rules, international rules.\", \"from\": 7252, \"to\": 7338, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The whole process is flawed.\", \"from\": 7340, \"to\": 7369, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From the conception of the test, to how the test was shared with us, to how the tests have become public, is so flawed that it's impossible to engage with it.\\\"\", \"from\": 7370, \"to\": 7529, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Khelif and Lin are both onto the next round of their competition and are both guaranteed\\u00a0medals in the Olympics.\", \"from\": 7531, \"to\": 7643, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is an excerpt from a report by Ryan Gaydos.\", \"from\": 7645, \"to\": 7693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7681, \"end\": 7685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"score\": 0.994204364164487, \"rank\": 0.0057901302580172535, \"text\": \"Ryan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10871364\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nolan_Ryan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Dutch Olympic men's volleyball team consisting of Steven van de Velde, who was convicted of raping a 12-year-old girl, and Matthew Immers were eliminated from Olympic medal contention on Sunday.\", \"from\": 7697, \"to\": 7895, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7701, \"end\": 7706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.8158411683295187, \"rank\": 0.20847788087724778, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}, {\"begin\": 7758, \"end\": 7770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999876297512182, \"rank\": 1.2370401759665e-05, \"text\": \"van de Velde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brazil defeated the Netherlands with a 21-16, 21-16 straight set win.\", \"from\": 7897, \"to\": 7966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7897, \"end\": 7903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.7358354586541093, \"rank\": 0.3484451850579297, \"text\": \"Brazil\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brazil_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 7917, \"end\": 7928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.45490689398822565, \"rank\": 0.790699304113937, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Van de Velde had been booed in every match he played in on Paris' sandy court in front of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 7968, \"to\": 8075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8027, \"end\": 8032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999367159917, \"rank\": 6.328405172201308e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was convicted of raping a 12-year-old British girl in 2016 and served 13 months n prison over it.\", \"from\": 8076, \"to\": 8176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8117, \"end\": 8124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.892540506034365, \"rank\": 0.1055373113119802, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Dutch officials allowed him to compete for an Olympic spot regardless.\", \"from\": 8177, \"to\": 8247, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8177, \"end\": 8182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"score\": 0.8158411683295187, \"rank\": 0.20847788087724778, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dutch_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Van de Velde did not walk through the mix zone to talk to reporters.\", \"from\": 8249, \"to\": 8317, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was an emotional roller coaster.\", \"from\": 8319, \"to\": 8355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I see it that way,\\\" Immers said.\", \"from\": 8356, \"to\": 8388, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We fought.\", \"from\": 8389, \"to\": 8400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We enjoyed every moment.\", \"from\": 8401, \"to\": 8425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So I am really proud of that.\", \"from\": 8426, \"to\": 8455, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the coolest stadium I ever played in.\", \"from\": 8456, \"to\": 8500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"...\", \"from\": 8501, \"to\": 8504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sad that we could not show our level.\", \"from\": 8505, \"to\": 8547, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But everything around it, I enjoyed it.\\\"\", \"from\": 8548, \"to\": 8588, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Immers said he and Van de Velde will remain a team with several tournaments still to come this year.\", \"from\": 8590, \"to\": 8690, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We still got a ninth on our first Olympics.\", \"from\": 8690, \"to\": 8734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I am proud of that,\\\" Immers said.\", \"from\": 8735, \"to\": 8772, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And we keep on going.\\\"\", \"from\": 8773, \"to\": 8796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Associated Press contributed to this report.\", \"from\": 8798, \"to\": 8846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8802, \"end\": 8818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9996870439197437, \"rank\": 0.000312989940732916, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Noah Lyles finally has hisOlympic goldmedal.After talking the talk for quite some time, the Gainesville, Fla., native is now walking the walk, as he won the men's 100-meter final on Sunday in Paris.\", \"from\": 8850, \"to\": 9048, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8850, \"end\": 8860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}, {\"begin\": 9042, \"end\": 9047, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.99998113761942, \"rank\": 1.8862735271393114e-05, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles crossed the finish line in 9.79784 seconds, a personal best, and winning by five-thousandths of a second.It appeared at first that Jamaica's Kishane Thompson had secured the win.\", \"from\": 9050, \"to\": 9234, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9205, \"end\": 9213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.9865040552457556, \"rank\": 0.01368053352630695, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The NBC broadcast even declared Thompson the winner until track officials reviewed the finish.\", \"from\": 9235, \"to\": 9329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9239, \"end\": 9242, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR_on_NBC\", \"score\": 0.8535550503803816, \"rank\": 0.09673822527704419, \"text\": \"NBC\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR_on_NBC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASCAR_on_NBC\"}, {\"begin\": 9267, \"end\": 9275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.6500941736029883, \"rank\": 0.5382386695740162, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lyles got his torso across the the line first before Thompson or his Team USA teammate Fred Kerley.\", \"from\": 9331, \"to\": 9430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9384, \"end\": 9392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"score\": 0.6500941736029883, \"rank\": 0.5382386695740162, \"text\": \"Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tina_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 9400, \"end\": 9408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 